    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Data asset that stores a Tryll workflow graph description. Equivalent to a Unity ScriptableObject holding node and wire lists.</para>
<para>Usage:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>In the Content Browser: right-click → Miscellaneous → Data Asset → TryllWorkflowAsset.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Edit nodes and routes in the Details panel.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Assign this asset to a <ref refid="class_u_tryll_agent_component" kindref="compound">UTryllAgentComponent</ref>&apos;s WorkflowAsset property.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>Programmatic alternative: populate <ref refid="struct_f_tryll_graph_description" kindref="compound">FTryllGraphDescription</ref> directly in C++ using <ref refid="struct_f_tryll_graph_builder" kindref="compound">FTryllGraphBuilder</ref>, or assign it to <ref refid="class_u_tryll_agent_component_1ad86b3d51d9b167a0532f44a929ab5472" kindref="member">UTryllAgentComponent::InlineGraphDescription</ref>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
